arChildNodes.szComment:
INT. ALDKIN'S SHACK/CELLAR

The PLAYER finishes slaying the demons in the cellar and crouches down to examine the place where the demons appeared. 
A shape, ALDKIN, jumps into frame in the rafters of the roof.   

As the player stands, Aldkin speaks, his voice deep and demonic.
The player looks up at Aldkin and he jumps to a different rafter to avoid being spotted.
Aldkin jumps down in front of the player with his arms raised, trying to make himself look imposing. Heâ€™s in demon form.

Aldkin pauses mid-sentence and looks down at the toy. 
He shifts back to his NORMAL form, caught off guard.
The player looks at the toy, and back at Aldkin.
Aldkin reaches out for the toy but the Player steps back.

Aldkin shakes his head and turns away.
The Player looks down at the toy in their hands and takes a step forward.
After Aldkin's question, the player nods and holds out the toy. Aldkin pauses a few seconds as he looks down it. Finally, he snatches the toy away and hugs it.
